pullRequest.body: Splits `Data/Finset/Image` into `Defs`+`Basic`+`Union`+`Range`, so definitions are not encumbered by unnecessary imports.

Yes, without this the `mod_cast` in 
```
theorem map_union [DecidableEq ] [DecidableEq ] {f :   } (s s : Finset ) :
    (s  s).map f = s.map f  s.map f :=
  mod_cast Set.image_union f s s

theorem map_inter [DecidableEq ] [DecidableEq ] {f :   } (s s : Finset ) :
    (s  s).map f = s.map f  s.map f :=
  mod_cast Set.image_inter f.injective (s := s) (t := s)
```
in `Mathlib.Data.Finset.Image.Basic` both fail.
